**shadcn-docs-nuxt** utilizes the [nuxt-og-image](https://nuxtseo.com/og-image/getting-started/installation) module to generate dynamic OG Images.

The dynamic OG Image is used in all pages **except** the index page. The index page uses a static OG Image defined in the [`ogImage`](/development/configuration/shadcn-docs#site) field instead.

## Using Built-in Templates

To use a template, set the name of the OG Image component in the [`ogImageComponent`](/development/configuration/shadcn-docs#site).

```ts [app.config.ts]
export default defineAppConfig({
  shadcnDocs: {
    site: {
      ogImageComponent: 'ShadcnDocs',
      ogImageColor: 'light', // or 'dark'
    },
  },
});
```

